6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Devin and Replit AI share a solid foundation of core features including Code Generation, Debugging, Multi Language, Chat. Where Devin pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Review and Refactoring and Test Generation and Documentation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Replit AI uniquely offers Autocomplete, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Devin holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Replit AI scores 7/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Replit AI comes in at a lower starting price of $25/mo, while Devin begins at $500/mo. Replit AI stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Devin requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
